        "details": {
            "description": "<p>A cheerful, wordless tune fills the room, compelling everyone to get to work.</p>",
            "disable": "<p><span data-pf2-check=\"religion\" data-pf2-traits=\"complex,haunt\" data-pf2-label=\"Exorcise Spirits DC\" data-pf2-dc=\"20\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Religion</span> (trained) to exorcise the spirits, or <span data-pf2-check=\"intimidation\" data-pf2-traits=\"complex,haunt\" data-pf2-label=\"Take a Break DC\" data-pf2-dc=\"21\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Intimidation</span> to convince the spirits it is time to take a break; three total successes are required to disable the haunt.</p>",
            "isComplex": false,
            "level": {
                "value": 3
            },
            "reset": "<p>The ghostly workers cease their routine 2 rounds after all living creatures leave the room and reset after 6 hours.</p>",
            "routine": "<p><span class=\"pf2-icon\">3</span> Ghostly workers appear in the room and begin abrading, scrubbing, and splashing cleaning chemicals on anyone in the area. Each creature in the room takes [[/r {1d4+2}[slashing]]]{1d4+2 slashing} and [[/r {1d4+2}[acid]]]{1d4+2 acid damage} (<span data-pf2-check=\"reflex\" data-pf2-traits=\"haunt,complex,damaging-effect\" data-pf2-label=\"Avoid Workers DC\" data-pf2-dc=\"20\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">basic Reflex</span> save; roll once for both).</p>"
